<br>
Now, I am not going to rise to this slapping and back-stabbing.  But I am going to give you a set of simple rules, I always abide by when it comes to raiding.<br>
After that, you decide what you should think or feel.<br>
<br>
If you don't agree with my policies, thats fine.  But, like someone we could all mention by now, you will end up disappointed - and regardless of how little this molehill was to begin with - look whats happened?  Mountains!<br>
<br>
Ok - see what you think..<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Expect to die.<br>
2. Expect to lose exp.<br>
3. Don't expect to win on drops.<br>
4. Don't expect to get what you're after!<br>
<br>
So why go in the first place?<br>
well, because you MAY live, you MAY gain some exp even - although raids are not about exp!<br>
You MAY win a drop of some value - who knows?<br>
Lastly, YOU MIGHT, just might get that epic piece you're after, or a piece of armour or new weapon that you've been after for soooo long!<br>
<br>
So, put simply, if any of the above rules don't apply to you after a raid - then you must of had a successful time!<br>
<br>
If you don't like it - don't go!  Its as simple as that.<br>
<br>
Oh, and just a word of support here - my guild has a few rogues capable of opening those doors now, and I also have a friend in another guild who would likely lend her set of lock picks to your cause, if she can.<br>
Thats if, you ever need a rogue, and are short of one!<br>
Shout me in game!  I'll try and help if I can...  Oh, and please, can I come too?<br>
<br>
Guildor Trackfinder<br>
58 Ranger - still in search of that ellusive Jade Reaver!<br>
